In case you missed it, here are the top News stories of the week: 1. Cyril's millions: GTI and Ford Ranger seized The cars bought with money stolen from President Cyril Ramaphosa's farm were reportedly seized by the Namibian authorities. 2. 'PASTOR told us to strip naked!' Church member Celia Govo (42) said they were instructed by the pastor to take off their clothes. "The pastor told us she had a vision that Jesus Christ was coming back,". 3. WHY son cut off mum's head and legs! The respected gogo had just retired from a lifetime of teaching and deserved a well-earned rest. But her son changed all of that when he allegedly murdered her because she wouldn't buy him a car. 4. HOSPITAL HORROR: Family wants R15m Onthatile Mororo's parents took him to the hospital for a minor burn injury to his left hand. But the two-year-old allegedly returned home with a injured right arm. 5. Notorious tsotsi killed in a hail of bullets On Sunday, 29 May, Gauteng cops issued a reward of up to R100 000 to anyone with information that could lead to the arrest and conviction of a wanted criminal, Mbuso Ndabazovela Biyela.